body:
When running apps, if there are analysis issues, should we increase the visibility of errors. THis could be:

- showing the Dart Analysis view
- opening a toast telling the users about the errors
- stopping the launch?

comment_data.body: Other mobile development contexts (e.g. Xcode or Android Studio) don't even let you run with compile errors (due to constraints of their development languages).  It's kinda neat that Dart does... but might cause confusion for the user.
Java Run Configurations perform a "build" pre-flight (which includes an error-check): we could consider something similar?

For example, you can proceed with the app launch but show a yellow balloon stuck to the Dart Analysis tool window saying that it contains errors.
We already show such a balloon to attract user attention when some error is printed to the Pub Serve tool window.

> you can proceed with the app launch but show a yellow balloon stuck to the Dart Analysis tool window

Sounds like a good solution! Do you have a link to the impl. for the pub server window? And what would the behavior be like if the user was not showing tool buttons?

> Do you have a link to the impl. for the pub server window?

see `PubServerService#NOTIFICATION_GROUP`

> And what would the behavior be like if the user was not showing tool buttons?

As I remember they are shown anyway while balloon is there

The resolution here is:

- show a notification if you run and there are errors
- force open of the Dart Analysis view

We should also show the notification on a reload.
We need to figure out the right state machine here so that we have a speed-bump if there are analysis issues, but it's not too intrusive to the user's workflow.
Work ongoing in the Dart Plugin.
One possible implementation is out for review here: https://github.com/JetBrains/intellij-plugins/pull/491.
We have a good lead on improved error notification on run.  Not for this Milestone though.

title: show analysis issues on app run
